meta data = tells search engine about page (title and description) -> but lacks inner page structure/content

schema markup = script which tells about page structure/context/meaning -> better search result (no title/description)

open graph = for sharing data on social (whatsapp - when link shared what image / title / description appears)

canonical version = what is official version of your website?

published date/ modified date = needed for blogs/article (not landing page) why? -> as no one cares about landing page published date
for faq updates it makes sense to update google about freshness 

---
robots.txt = for telling google bot about links to explore ,is used by web crawlers as they keep hitting website for seo,

why -> if not mentioned (now google decides what to crawl) this files indirectly help google faster crawling and better ranking
---

sitemap = tells google to index pages within local url -> internationalschooling.org/abc

--- 
href lang -> tells google about for different language url are these 

---

robot-tags -> index, follow == for indexing pages and following links on pages 


---

